    <br><br /><br><br /><br><br /><br><br /><br><br /><br><br /><br>   
    Flea market season is upon us and New York City is active in participating!  As a result, it’s no surprise that NYC locals have taken the concept of flea markets and brought it to the next level by creating a new style of flea markets — all about food. Smorgasburg is an outdoor all-food market occurring at various waterfront locations every Saturday and Sunday, running from April to November from 11am to 6pm."
    <br /><br />
    The “Woodstock of Eating,” as coined by The New York Times, attracts over 100 vendors providing unique and crafty treats to the foodies that come from near and far.
    <br /><br />
    The idea of Smorgasburg was developed by Eric Demby and Jonathan Butler, who also founded the wildly successful Brooklyn Flea; a standard style outdoor flea market.
    <br /><br />
